SIMPLE: holdback
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Holdback
<hw>Hold"back`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Check;
hindrance; restraint; obstacle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The only <qex>holdback</qex> is the affection . . . that we bear
to our wealth.</q> <rj><qau>Hammond.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The projection or loop on the thill of a vehicle. to
which a strap of the harness is attached, to hold back a carriage when
going down hill, or in backing; also, the strap or part of the harness
so used.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Holder</ent>⟦br⟧
